# Mugi, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Mugi (; Dargwa: МухIи) is a rural locality (a selo) in Akushinsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 3,372 as of 2010. There are 11 streets.
Geography
Mugi is located 11&nbsp;km northeast of Akusha (the district's administrative centre) by road. Zilmukmakhi is the nearest rural locality.
